Hepatocellular carcinoma. Part 1. General considerations and diagnosis. Several aspects are revised on the subject hepatocellular carcinoma related to its incidence/prevalence, risk and prognostic factors, cellular proliferation, pathological aspects, progression of chronic hepatitis B and C to cirrhosis and hepatocellular carcinoma, natural course of hepatocellular carcinoma, some clinical data, morphological diagnosis with special emphasis on radiological findings as ultrasound, dynamic computed tomography and magnetic resonance imaging, color-power Doppler, tissue and contrast harmonic.